"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-europe-2024-0307-1436516-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"French public sector workers will strike during the July-August Paris Olympics, the heavyweight CGT union federation has said, adding it would file formal strike notices next month.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9477256587172201, \"rank\": 0.054263075522067314, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 96, \"end\": 99, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8689201597120717e-14, \"text\": \"CGT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our warnings must finally be heard,\\\" CGT chief Sophie Binet told broadcaster Franceinfo, saying vital questions such as overtime work, lodging and childcare facilities had not been addressed.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 221, \"end\": 224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8689201597120717e-14, \"text\": \"CGT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_of_the_Argentines\"}, {\"begin\": 231, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"score\": 0.5764941821349139, \"rank\": 0.6542277230503923, \"text\": \"Sophie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\"}, {\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 2.1046298782921643e-12, \"text\": \"Binet\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\"}, {\"begin\": 261, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Info_(TV_channel)\", \"score\": 0.9103691617321688, \"rank\": 0.07407407407407474, \"text\": \"Franceinfo\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Info_(TV_channel)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_Info_(TV_channel)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The strike notice would cover people working in central and local government, as well as medical and social workers.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Hundreds of thousands of workers will be battered by the Games,\\\" Ms Binet said, including with overtime and restrictions on taking time off.\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are asking what will be the social conditions of this work, how will all the workers who have to come to the Paris region for the Olympics be housed?\\\"\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999814870082, \"rank\": 1.8512880010308973e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"she added.\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"How will their children be taken care of when it's the school holidays at the same time?\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What bonuses will they get?\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So far nothing has been sorted out on this side.\\\"\", \"from\": 923, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The announcement follows a call last month for a \\\"social truce\\\" without strikes from Paris Olympics organising committee chief Tony Estanguet.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1116, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1059, \"end\": 1073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, Ms Binet on Sunday demanded a meeting with Prime Minister Gabriel Attal to discuss the issue.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"score\": 0.9999999999979536, \"rank\": 2.1046298782921643e-12, \"text\": \"Binet\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Binet\"}, {\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only a few public sector workers have been told what support they will get during the Games, with Interior Minister Gerald Darmanin saying police working in the Paris region will get a bonus of up to \\u20ac1,900.\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1320, \"end\": 1337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9666106889625549, \"rank\": 0.03210767800246919, \"text\": \"Interior Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"score\": 0.9504570071645827, \"rank\": 0.05171787054106958, \"text\": \"Gerald\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\"}, {\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999814870082, \"rank\": 1.8512880010308973e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Talks have started in other fields on compensating overtime and missed holidays, including for hospital and transport workers.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:AFP  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1582, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1608, \"end\": 1631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851268295, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 1633, \"end\": 1640, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999777987798, \"rank\": 2.220108014218702e-08, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbped